there's the canonical momentum.

581
00:23:24,770 --> 00:23:28,010
The canonical momentum is the derivative of the Lagrangian

582
00:23:28,010 --> 00:23:29,070
with respect to the velocity.

583
00:23:29,550 --> 00:23:30,310
So p,

584
00:23:30,310 --> 00:23:31,290
in this case,

585
00:23:31,290 --> 00:23:32,610
is just equal to m x dot,

586
00:23:32,730 --> 00:23:34,070
just exactly what you'd expect.

587
00:23:35,710 --> 00:23:38,690
If we multiply that by q dot,

588
00:23:38,870 --> 00:23:41,190
in this case there's only one coordinate in the problem,

589
00:23:41,389 --> 00:23:42,110
just x.

590
00:23:42,610 --> 00:23:45,610
Then we would get p x dot,

591
00:23:45,770 --> 00:23:48,370
which would just be m x dot squared,

592
00:23:50,270 --> 00:23:55,230
one x dot comes from the q dot,

593
00:23:55,390 --> 00:23:57,010
the other one comes from the p,

594
00:23:57,850 --> 00:24:00,030
so it's m x dot squared,

595
00:24:00,310 --> 00:24:02,810
and then minus the Lagrangian.

596
00:24:03,090 --> 00:24:03,690
So,

597
00:24:03,690 --> 00:24:05,330
minus this term,

598
00:24:06,409 --> 00:24:08,970
minus one half m x dot squared,

599
00:24:10,970 --> 00:24:11,810
this one,

600
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:14,490
and then minus minus v,

601
00:24:14,490 --> 00:24:15,610
or plus v.

602
00:24:18,850 --> 00:24:21,570
Two minus signs giving you a plus sign.

603
00:24:22,030 --> 00:24:22,630
Okay,

604
00:24:22,630 --> 00:24:24,420
the m x dot squared and the

605
00:24:24,420 --> 00:24:26,210
minus a half m x dot squared

606
00:24:26,210 --> 00:24:29,110
just give you plus m x dot,

607
00:24:29,110 --> 00:24:30,690
half m x dot squared.

608
00:24:31,190 --> 00:24:31,790
So,

609
00:24:31,790 --> 00:24:32,590
what do you get?

610
00:24:33,310 --> 00:24:37,510
You get the sum of kinetic energy plus potential energy.

611
00:24:39,530 --> 00:24:40,730
Just the definition.

612
00:24:40,970 --> 00:24:44,870
The definition of potential energy and kinetic energy,

613
00:24:45,090 --> 00:24:46,730
in the case where they apply,

614
00:24:46,730 --> 00:24:49,970
where you can separate the Lagrangian nicely into

615
00:24:51,390 --> 00:24:54,690
quadratic things in coordinate and time derivatives,

616
00:24:54,970 --> 00:24:58,030
and other pieces which don't depend on time derivatives.

617
00:24:58,570 --> 00:25:01,830
It's in that case where there's things which are

618
00:25:03,290 --> 00:25:05,070
quadratic in time derivatives,

619
00:25:05,350 --> 00:25:08,350
and other things which don't contain time derivatives,

620
00:25:08,590 --> 00:25:10,590
that there's a well-defined separation

621
00:25:11,429 --> 00:25:13,770
into kinetic energy and potential energy.

622
00:25:13,770 --> 00:25:18,670
The kinetic energy is just the quadratic expression

623
00:25:18,670 --> 00:25:20,010
in terms of velocities.

624
00:25:20,470 --> 00:25:24,630
The potential energy is the piece in the Lagrangian

625
00:25:24,630 --> 00:25:27,270
which doesn't depend on time derivatives.

626
00:25:27,690 --> 00:25:28,530
That's it.

627
00:25:28,930 --> 00:25:31,150
Notice that in the Hamiltonian,

628
00:25:31,770 --> 00:25:33,150
the energy,

629
00:25:33,150 --> 00:25:34,730
it's t,

630
00:25:34,730 --> 00:25:35,910
or kinetic energy,

631
00:25:36,050 --> 00:25:37,350
plus potential energy,

632
00:25:37,630 --> 00:25:38,850
and the Lagrangian,

633
00:25:38,850 --> 00:25:41,070
it's kinetic energy minus potential energy.

634
00:25:41,590 --> 00:25:42,350
So,

635
00:25:42,350 --> 00:25:43,090
in any case,

636
00:25:43,090 --> 00:25:45,170
if the Lagrangian is of the simple form

637
00:25:45,840 --> 00:25:50,310
of squares of velocities,

638
00:25:50,330 --> 00:25:51,910
plus things which don't,

639
00:25:51,910 --> 00:25:54,130
or minus things which don't depend on velocities,

640
00:25:54,370 --> 00:25:56,650
you can usually read off very quickly,

641
00:25:56,730 --> 00:25:57,710
without doing any work,

642
00:25:57,970 --> 00:26:02,330
what the Hamiltonian is from the Lagrangian.

643
00:26:02,390 --> 00:26:06,030
You just change the sign of the term

644
00:26:06,860 --> 00:26:09,010
which doesn't contain velocities.

645
00:26:10,050 --> 00:26:10,690
That's it.

646
00:26:10,750 --> 00:26:11,510
That's the whole prescription.

647
00:26:11,510 --> 00:26:14,770
And we can use that,

648
00:26:14,850 --> 00:26:18,570
but we should remember that it really comes from that.

649
00:26:18,990 --> 00:26:21,210
What was the point of this Hamiltonian?

650
00:26:21,350 --> 00:26:24,290
The point of this Hamiltonian is it's very easy,

651
00:26:24,430 --> 00:26:26,490
go back to your classical mechanics notes,

652
00:26:26,610 --> 00:26:28,210
using Lagrange's equations

653
00:26:28,890 --> 00:26:31,230
to prove that this is conserved,

654
00:26:31,410 --> 00:26:32,730
that it doesn't change with time,

655
00:26:33,370 --> 00:26:34,750
that the equations of motion,

656
00:26:35,830 --> 00:26:37,310
Lagrangian equations of motion,

657
00:26:37,390 --> 00:26:39,290
applied to everything on this side here,

658
00:26:39,510 --> 00:26:41,430
will tell you that,

659
00:26:41,510 --> 00:26:43,470
the Hamiltonian is conserved,

660
00:26:43,590 --> 00:26:45,650
and it is of course the energy.

661
00:26:45,850 --> 00:26:47,050
It is of course the energy

662
00:26:47,050 --> 00:26:49,790
expressed in a somewhat unfamiliar form.

663
00:26:50,070 --> 00:26:50,990
Total energy.

664
00:26:52,250 --> 00:26:52,890
Okay,

665
00:26:52,890 --> 00:26:54,850
now let's come to field theory.

666
00:26:56,130 --> 00:26:58,630
Field theory is a special case

667
00:26:58,630 --> 00:27:01,150
of ordinary classical mechanics,

668
00:27:02,870 --> 00:27:04,150
slightly obscured

669
00:27:04,150 --> 00:27:07,530
when we try to write it in relativistic fashion.

670
00:27:08,390 --> 00:27:10,750
If we want to see the close connection

671
00:27:10,750 --> 00:27:14,110
between field theory and classical mechanics,

672
00:27:14,410 --> 00:27:18,090
it is best to give up this whole enterprise

673
00:27:18,090 --> 00:27:21,930
of trying to keep all equations explicitly invariant

674
00:27:21,930 --> 00:27:22,950
under Lorentz transformation,

675
00:27:23,370 --> 00:27:24,670
and to just say,

676
00:27:24,750 --> 00:27:26,830
let's pick somebody's time,

677
00:27:27,569 --> 00:27:30,230
your time or my time,

678
00:27:30,450 --> 00:27:32,590
but pick a time variable,

679
00:27:32,810 --> 00:27:33,210
in other words,

680
00:27:33,210 --> 00:27:34,450
pick a frame of reference

681
00:27:34,450 --> 00:27:36,410
and stick with that frame of reference,

682
00:27:36,670 --> 00:27:38,870
and don't for the moment worry about

683
00:27:38,870 --> 00:27:40,690
going back and forth between different frames

684
00:27:40,750 --> 00:27:41,210
of reference.

685
00:27:42,110 --> 00:27:43,150
We'll do that later.

686
00:27:43,350 --> 00:27:44,690
Pick a frame of reference,

687
00:27:44,950 --> 00:27:45,850
pick a time,

688
00:27:46,610 --> 00:27:48,750
don't try to keep the equations invariant

689
00:27:49,510 --> 00:27:50,590
under Lorentz transformation,

690
00:27:51,910 --> 00:27:54,650
and it is easier in that form

691
00:27:54,650 --> 00:27:57,150
to see the connection with classical mechanics.

692
00:27:57,650 --> 00:27:58,170
Okay,

693
00:27:58,170 --> 00:27:58,650
so let me,

694
00:27:58,730 --> 00:27:59,630
well I'll leave this up here,

695
00:27:59,710 --> 00:28:01,050
but let's come over to here.

696
00:28:01,950 --> 00:28:02,570
All right,

697
00:28:02,570 --> 00:28:03,410
classical mechanics,

698
00:28:03,690 --> 00:28:04,890
you have a time axis,

699
00:28:05,630 --> 00:28:07,110
and you have a collection of things,

700
00:28:07,210 --> 00:28:09,070
q sub i of t,

701
00:28:09,070 --> 00:28:12,350
and you have an action principle.

702
00:28:12,690 --> 00:28:14,870
The action principle is

703
00:28:17,330 --> 00:28:19,750
Lagrangian as a function of q and q dot,

704
00:28:20,310 --> 00:28:22,290
or all the q's and q dots,

705
00:28:22,370 --> 00:28:22,950
dt.

706
00:28:24,350 --> 00:28:25,370
That's the action,

707
00:28:26,710 --> 00:28:29,510
and the action principle is the principle of least action.

708
00:28:29,690 --> 00:28:30,210
That's it,

709
00:28:30,210 --> 00:28:30,830
a time axis,

710
00:28:31,110 --> 00:28:33,870
a set of coordinates which depend on the time axis,

711
00:28:34,130 --> 00:28:36,610
an expression for the action,

712
00:28:36,690 --> 00:28:38,250
which is an integral over time,

713
00:28:38,250 --> 00:28:43,530
and a principle variation of the action,

714
00:28:43,630 --> 00:28:45,870
or the action is a stationary point.

715
00:28:46,130 --> 00:28:46,730
All right,

716
00:28:46,730 --> 00:28:48,650
so now to go from here to field theory,

717
00:28:49,890 --> 00:28:50,390
again,

718
00:28:50,390 --> 00:28:51,650
we have a time axis,

719
00:28:52,490 --> 00:28:54,710
and the coordinates of the system

720
00:28:55,250 --> 00:28:56,630
are functions of time.

721
00:28:56,830 --> 00:28:58,710
But what are the coordinates of the system?

722
00:28:58,770 --> 00:29:00,370
The coordinates of the system

723
00:29:00,370 --> 00:29:04,470
are not labeled by a discrete index i,

724
00:29:04,790 --> 00:29:07,910
the coordinates of the system are labeled by position,

725
00:29:07,910 --> 00:29:09,910
they are the values of the fields

726
00:29:09,910 --> 00:29:11,650
at each position in space.

727
00:29:11,990 --> 00:29:13,510
If we wanted to,

728
00:29:13,710 --> 00:29:18,270
we could imagine that space was discrete,

729
00:29:22,130 --> 00:29:24,850
and have x go horizontally,

730
00:29:25,670 --> 00:29:29,350
but the only relevant points

731
00:29:29,350 --> 00:29:31,510
would be some discrete collection of points,

732
00:29:31,810 --> 00:29:34,750
and then say the values of the fields

733
00:29:34,750 --> 00:29:36,330
at each position

734
00:29:36,970 --> 00:29:38,310
would define a coordinate.

735
00:29:38,830 --> 00:29:39,970
The field over here,

736
00:29:40,050 --> 00:29:40,770
the field over here,

737
00:29:40,830 --> 00:29:41,570
the field over here,

738
00:29:41,610 --> 00:29:42,330
the field over here,

739
00:29:42,390 --> 00:29:42,890
and so forth.

740
00:29:43,250 --> 00:29:44,030
This would be,

741
00:29:44,090 --> 00:29:45,310
this might be called phi zero,

742
00:29:45,550 --> 00:29:46,690
this might be called phi one,

743
00:29:46,790 --> 00:29:47,850
this might be called phi two,

744
00:29:47,910 --> 00:29:48,350
and so forth.

745
00:29:48,510 --> 00:29:49,650
And the q's,

746
00:29:49,830 --> 00:29:51,430
the canonical coordinates,

747
00:29:51,470 --> 00:29:52,830
would be the phi's.

748
00:29:53,450 --> 00:29:55,470
And instead of writing phi i

749
00:29:56,189 --> 00:30:00,190
to indicate which green line the phi is on,

750
00:30:00,770 --> 00:30:03,970
I'll just accept the fact that there's an x axis,

751
00:30:04,210 --> 00:30:05,630
and write phi of x.

752
00:30:06,970 --> 00:30:08,350
So at each point x,

753
00:30:08,470 --> 00:30:10,990
there's a separate and independent field,

754
00:30:11,190 --> 00:30:13,790
or a separate and independent coordinate.

755
00:30:13,990 --> 00:30:15,610
Now I don't use coordinate to mean x,

756
00:30:15,810 --> 00:30:17,030
I mean to use coordinate in

757
00:30:17,030 --> 00:30:18,250
the same sense that we use q.

758
00:30:18,790 --> 00:30:19,690
Degree of freedom.

759
00:30:19,970 --> 00:30:21,910
Perhaps degree of freedom is a better word.

760
00:30:22,430 --> 00:30:22,870
Yeah,

761
00:30:22,870 --> 00:30:24,050
let's call it degree of freedom.

762
00:30:24,230 --> 00:30:25,790
Phi of x is a degree of freedom,

763
00:30:25,910 --> 00:30:27,490
and x is simply a label,

764
00:30:27,670 --> 00:30:30,290
in the same sense that i is a label.

765
00:30:31,610 --> 00:30:32,050
Okay,

766
00:30:32,050 --> 00:30:33,090
so we shouldn't get confused

767
00:30:33,090 --> 00:30:34,590
between coordinates and labels.

768
00:30:36,350 --> 00:30:37,130
There's also,

769
00:30:37,130 --> 00:30:37,750
of course,

770
00:30:37,850 --> 00:30:39,230
time derivatives.

771
00:30:42,870 --> 00:30:44,370
Those are like the q dots.

772
00:30:45,570 --> 00:30:47,810
Now Lagrangians also depend

773
00:30:47,810 --> 00:30:51,210
not only on phi at each point,

774
00:30:51,410 --> 00:30:54,050
but they also depend on derivatives

775
00:30:54,050 --> 00:30:55,350
with respect to space.

776
00:30:55,630 --> 00:30:56,970
Let's think about that for a moment.

777
00:30:57,330 --> 00:30:58,170
In other words,

778
00:30:58,190 --> 00:31:01,610
they depend on things like d phi by dx.

779
00:31:02,150 --> 00:31:03,390
Not d phi by dt,

780
00:31:03,650 --> 00:31:04,570
but d phi by dx.

781
00:31:05,450 --> 00:31:07,270
Typical Lagrangian density,

782
00:31:08,290 --> 00:31:10,350
typical Lagrangian for a field theory.

783
00:31:10,850 --> 00:31:13,450
But what is phi,

784
00:31:13,730 --> 00:31:15,650
derivative of phi with respect to x?

785
00:31:16,910 --> 00:31:17,910
What is it?

786
00:31:18,450 --> 00:31:20,330
It's really another way of writing,

787
00:31:22,090 --> 00:31:24,430
let's say the distance between these points

788
00:31:24,430 --> 00:31:25,250
is called epsilon,

789
00:31:25,650 --> 00:31:26,790
where epsilon is small.

790
00:31:27,110 --> 00:31:29,010
It's really a way of writing phi

791
00:31:29,580 --> 00:31:31,730
at a point x plus epsilon,

792
00:31:32,870 --> 00:31:33,890
minus phi,

793
00:31:34,770 --> 00:31:36,250
at a point x,

794
00:31:36,370 --> 00:31:38,030
divided by epsilon.

795
00:31:38,870 --> 00:31:40,250
And so the derivative

796
00:31:40,250 --> 00:31:43,710
is really just a function of the phi's.

797
00:31:43,790 --> 00:31:44,330
It doesn't,

798
00:31:44,330 --> 00:31:45,290
the most important thing is

799
00:31:45,290 --> 00:31:46,750
it doesn't involve phi dot.

800
00:31:47,370 --> 00:31:49,810
So in places where the Lagrangian

801
00:31:49,810 --> 00:31:51,990
might depend on spatial derivatives,

802
00:31:52,630 --> 00:31:54,690
that's really part of its dependence

803
00:31:54,690 --> 00:31:55,870
on the phi's.

804
00:31:56,070 --> 00:31:56,810
In this case,

805
00:31:56,830 --> 00:31:58,030
it might depend on two phi's

806
00:31:58,030 --> 00:31:58,850
at the same time,

807
00:31:59,770 --> 00:32:01,190
but there's nothing to say

808
00:32:01,190 --> 00:32:03,170
that a Lagrangian can't depend on

809
00:32:03,170 --> 00:32:04,570
two q's at the same time.

810
00:32:04,570 --> 00:32:07,310
It could depend on q1 minus q2,

811
00:32:07,429 --> 00:32:08,350
or something like that.

812
00:32:08,530 --> 00:32:11,990
Here it's depending on phi at one point

813
00:32:11,990 --> 00:32:13,330
minus phi at the other point.

814
00:32:13,610 --> 00:32:14,090
So,

815
00:32:14,090 --> 00:32:14,370
yeah.

816
00:32:14,750 --> 00:32:18,030
So you've got phi dot of x.

817
00:32:18,230 --> 00:32:18,449
Yeah.

818
00:32:18,550 --> 00:32:21,370
So phi's not explicitly a function of phi.

819
00:32:21,510 --> 00:32:21,669
No,

820
00:32:21,669 --> 00:32:21,770
no,

821
00:32:21,770 --> 00:32:22,490
it's not explicitly.

822
00:32:22,830 --> 00:32:23,050
No,

823
00:32:23,050 --> 00:32:23,449
it is,

824
00:32:23,449 --> 00:32:23,790
it is,

825
00:32:23,810 --> 00:32:24,270
whoa,

826
00:32:24,270 --> 00:32:24,590
whoa,

827
00:32:24,590 --> 00:32:24,650
whoa,

828
00:32:24,650 --> 00:32:24,990
be careful.

829
00:32:25,810 --> 00:32:28,010
It's not depending on time

830
00:32:28,010 --> 00:32:29,550
because x depends on time.

831
00:32:29,670 --> 00:32:30,810
x is just a label.

832
00:32:32,090 --> 00:32:33,350
x is just a label.

833
00:32:34,570 --> 00:32:34,850
We could,

834
00:32:34,850 --> 00:32:37,470
instead of calling this the x-axis,

835
00:32:37,650 --> 00:32:39,770
we could call it the numerical axis i,

836
00:32:40,630 --> 00:32:43,150
and this would be phi of phi i.

837
00:32:43,750 --> 00:32:45,850
So why don't you write phi of x and t?

838
00:32:46,590 --> 00:32:47,030
Yeah,

839
00:32:47,030 --> 00:32:47,470
that's right.

840
00:32:47,590 --> 00:32:49,530
Phi is in general a function of x and t,

841
00:32:50,790 --> 00:32:53,390
in the same sense that

842
00:32:53,390 --> 00:32:55,990
q depends on i and t.

843
00:32:56,670 --> 00:32:59,390
It depends on i just because it depends

844
00:32:59,390 --> 00:33:00,630
on which one you're talking about.

845
00:33:00,670 --> 00:33:01,410
You're talking about q1,

846
00:33:01,470 --> 00:33:02,370
you're talking about q2.

847
00:33:03,290 --> 00:33:03,750
Here,

848
00:33:03,750 --> 00:33:06,690
are you talking about phi at one point,

849
00:33:06,750 --> 00:33:08,430
or are you talking about phi at another point?

850
00:33:08,550 --> 00:33:09,650
Just one more follow-up.

851
00:33:09,730 --> 00:33:11,510
So you treat each one of those phi's

852
00:33:11,510 --> 00:33:12,590
as an independent variable?

853
00:33:12,790 --> 00:33:13,830
You treat each one of them

854
00:33:13,830 --> 00:33:16,910
as an independent canonical degree of freedom.

855
00:33:17,290 --> 00:33:19,190
What about the sort of continuity constraints?

856
00:33:20,770 --> 00:33:21,370
All right,

857
00:33:21,370 --> 00:33:22,510
that's a very good question.

858
00:33:22,610 --> 00:33:23,550
That's a very good question.

859
00:33:23,730 --> 00:33:25,660
And the answer is if you

860
00:33:25,660 --> 00:33:27,590
write the right kind of Lagrangian

861
00:33:27,590 --> 00:33:29,710
or the right kind of Hamiltonian,

862
00:33:30,570 --> 00:33:32,350
then sudden abrupt change

863
00:33:32,370 --> 00:33:34,850
in phi from one point to another

864
00:33:34,850 --> 00:33:36,630
will be very costly in energy.

